18, 2020 at 11:13 a.m.SALT LAKE CITY — Saturday's numbers from the Utah Department of Health show 126 new cases of COVID-19 and two new coronavirus-related deaths.
That brings the Utah totals to 2,931 confirmed cases, with 25 total deaths from the disease.
The total number of cases reported by the health department includes all cases of COVID-19 since Utah’s outbreak began, including those who are infected now, those who have recovered from the disease, and those who have died.
One was a female Utah County resident, and the other was a male Salt Lake County resident.
Salt Lake County has more than half of the state's coronavirus cases at 1,547 total; Utah County has had 417, and Summit County has 316.